<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/89d13ad50c99b43ed0f03569754f36aa.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 2 and c = 5. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.6</li><li>23.6</li><li>66.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={2}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{25}={4}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{25}-{4}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{21}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{21}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4.5825756949558}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4.6}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{5}}\right)}}}\approx{23.578178478202}\approx{23.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{5}}\right)}}}\approx{66.421821521798}\approx{66.4}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

